hich will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 604489711, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2MDQ0ODk3MTE=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-NLL", "name": "A-NLL", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Non Lexical Lifetimes (NLL)"}, {"id": 867465703, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw4Njc0NjU3MDM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/NLL-complete", "name": "NLL-complete", "color": "f799ea", "default": false, "description": "Working towards the \"valid code works\" goal"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 19, "created_at": "2018-10-11T09:53:42Z", "updated_at": "2019-08-15T22:06:53Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Spawned off of #21232\r\n\r\nIn the long-term, we want to accept code like this:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nstruct S { x: u32, y: u32 }\r\nfn main() { let mut s: S; s.x = 10; s.y = 30; a_use_of(&s); another_use_of(s); }\r\nfn a_use_of(_s: &S) { /* ... */ }\r\nfn another_use_of(_s: S) { /* ... */ }\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe probably *also* want to start accepting this too:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nstruct S { x: u32, y: u32 }\r\nfn main() { let mut s: S; s.x = 10; a_use_of_field(s.x); }\r\nfn a_use_of_field(_x: u32) { /* ... */ }\r\n```\r\n\r\n(But that second example is more debatable. I don't think there's any debate about the first example.)\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nSee #54986 for the short-term goal of rejecting all partial initializations until we can actually *use* the results you get from partial initialization.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/54987/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/54987/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}